## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: Django 5.1
- **Database**: PostgreSQL 17
- **Cache**: Redis 7
- **Package Manager**: uv
- **Testing**: pytest + pytest-django
- **Formatting**: ruff

## Project Structure

- `{{.ProjectName}}/` - Django project package (settings, urls, wsgi)
- `{{.ProjectName}}/settings/base.py` - Shared settings
- `{{.ProjectName}}/settings/local.py` - Local development overrides
- `apps/` - Django applications (create new apps here)
- `tests/` - Test suite
- `static/` - Static assets
- `docs/supporting/` - Supporting documentation

## Development Commands

```bash
make start       # Start Docker Compose stack
make stop        # Stop all services
make bash        # Shell into web container
make shell       # Django interactive shell
make test        # Run pytest suite
make migrate     # Run database migrations
make superuser   # Create admin superuser
make reqs        # Compile requirements
```

## Conventions

- Use UUID primary keys for models exposed in URLs
- Settings split into base.py (shared) and local.py (dev overrides)
- All new features go in `apps/` as Django apps
- Tests go in `tests/` directory, not next to source files
- Use `ruff` for code formatting
- Use type hints for function signatures
